<Defs>

  <StatDef>
	<defName>WVC_PawnMechanoidization</defName>
	<label>genetic mechanoidization</label>
	<description>Determines how far mechanoidization has gone. The higher the values, the worse non-mecha pawns treat the carrier of genes. Also, a higher mechanoidization parameter slightly reduces the chance of a nervous breakdown.

Values below 5 have no effect and the pawn is treated as a human. All values above begin to lower the opinion of others. Mecha-pawns also dislike those more mechanized than them, but not as much as non-mechs. The mechanoidization opinion debuff stacks with implant and gene modification opinions.

Transhumanists, body modders and mechanitors ignore mechanoidization. Body purists always have the most negative attitude towards mechanoidization. The blind also do not respond to mechanoidization.

Some mecha-genes also affect how the debuff is calculated. For example "Natural enemy" increases the debuff, while "Perfect shape" reduces it.

The effect appears only at very low and higher expectations.

Some genes have a bonus to mechanoidization which is marked as (mechalike), this bonus only triggers when a mechaskin is present.

This parameter is affected only by mecha-genes.</description>
	<category>PawnSocial</category>
	<defaultBaseValue>0</defaultBaseValue>
	<hideAtValue>0</hideAtValue>
	<minValue>0.0</minValue>
	<!-- A pawn cannot be more than 50% mechanoid-like, too few mecha-genes -->
	<!-- Пешка не может быть мехой больше чем на 50%, слишком мало меха-генов -->
	<maxValue>100</maxValue>
	<showOnAnimals>false</showOnAnimals>
	<showOnMechanoids>false</showOnMechanoids>
	<!-- <showIfUndefined>false</showIfUndefined> -->
	<!-- <showZeroBaseValue>false</showZeroBaseValue> -->
	<!-- <showOnDefaultValue>false</showOnDefaultValue> -->
	<scenarioRandomizable>false</scenarioRandomizable>
	<forInformationOnly>true</forInformationOnly>
	<alwaysHide>false</alwaysHide>
	<toStringStyle>FloatOne</toStringStyle>
	<displayPriorityInCategory>2000</displayPriorityInCategory>
  </StatDef>

